detailedDescription.articleBody:
Isabelle Lendl is an American amateur golfer. She finished second in the 2006 American Junior Golf Association girls standings. She ranked first in the Top Fives and was named a first team Rolex Junior All-American. Her father is Ivan Lendl, a member of the International Tennis Hall of Fame. She speaks two languages - Czech and English.
She was the youngest player to qualify for the 2004 U.S. Women's Amateur at the age of 12.
